{"updated_at": {"date": {"d": "26", "m": "06", "Y": "2026"}, "time": {"H": "07", "M": "40", "S": "16"}}, "news": [{"title": "Ranchi civic body sets seven-day deadline for fire NOC, Bokaro orders safety audit", "para": "Following a deadly fire in Lucknow, Ranchi and Bokaro authorities are cracking down on fire safety. Property owners in Ranchi have seven days to get Fire No Objection Certificates or face sealing. Bokaro is conducting a comprehensive audit of coaching centres and other establishments, highlighting serious gaps like inadequate exits and a lack of NOCs, with strict action promised for non-compliance.", "href": "https://realty.economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/industry/ranchi-civic-body-imposes-urgent-fire-safety-measures-following-tragic-blaze-in-lucknow/132008799?utm_source=newslisting&utm_medium=latestNews", "img": "data:image/png;base64, ", "img-src": "https://etimg.etb2bimg.com/thumb/img-size-624164/132008799.cms?width=150&height=112", "tag": "industry"}, {"title": "Dharwad: Consumer panel raps developers, orders relief to senior citizen in plot registration row", "para": "A senior citizen in Dharwad has won a significant victory against developers who refused to register her residential plot despite receiving substantial payment. The District Consumer Disputes Redressal Commission ordered the developers to allot an alternative plot and execute the sale deed within a month. They must also pay Rs 50,000 in compensation and Rs 10,000 for litigation costs, ensuring justice for the aggrieved buyer.", "href": "https://realty.economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/regulatory/dharwad-consumer-panel-raps-developers-orders-relief-to-senior-citizen-in-plot-registration-row/132006911?utm_source=newslisting&utm_medium=latestNews", "img": "data:image/png;base64, ", "img-src": "https://etimg.etb2bimg.com/thumb/img-size-333169/132006911.cms?width=150&height=112", "tag": "regulatory"}, {"title": "Dubai\u2019s housing market cools after long red-hot five-year rally", "para": "Dubai\u2019s residential property market is cooling after a five-year rally as buyers become more price-sensitive, negotiate harder and shift toward smaller, lower-cost homes amid higher supply and geopolitical uncertainty. While prices remain higher year-on-year, they have softened quarterly, with annual growth slowing sharply from 17\u201318% in 2024 to around 4\u20135%.", "href": "https://realty.economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/international/dubai-housing-market-cools-prices-fall-after-5-year-surge/132007215?utm_source=newslisting&utm_medium=latestNews", "img": "data:image/png;base64, ", "img-src": "https://etimg.etb2bimg.com/thumb/img-size-1394501/132007215.cms?width=150&height=112", "tag": "international"}]}